W8 / F6 -- Safari Web Extension staging directory.

ORM stages the signed + notarised + stapled Safari extension artefact here at
cut time, from CM020's build output:

    (in CM020)  xcodegen generate && bin/build-safari-extension.sh
    then        cp dist/OstlerSafariExtension-<version>.app.zip \
                   vendor/extensions/OstlerSafariExtension.app.zip

The artefact MUST be Developer-ID signed (team V95N2B8X7A) + notarised +
stapled. A --dry-run (unsigned) artefact fails Gatekeeper and must never ship.

The .app.zip itself is gitignored (binary, signed-per-cut). Both release.sh
(tarball path) and gui/project.yml (DMG .app path) read it from this directory
and fail loudly if it is absent, so the gap that left it silently unstaged
cannot recur.
